{"$ambrosia":"aero:interactive:9417ac60-5f60-11ea-8e69-affb2224d7e8:*","$id":"09bc6ca0-44e0-11ed-88c7-33cd0ef5e6fb","$workspaceId":"7fff47c0-44d6-11ed-bcef-d5307f42495c","$projectId":"86cb0040-44df-11ed-8442-dbcbc27803ca","annotations":[],"configSchemaVersion":"/pluginGenericSchema/v1","config":{"stage":{"sections":[{"rowsAreFullWidth":false,"backgroundImageUrl":"","rows":[{"columns":[{"stageElements":[{"type":"stage-element-text","value":{"object":"value","document":{"object":"document","data":{},"nodes":[{"object":"block","type":"heading-two","ref":"b54930f7-76b3-4ccc-b21e-9715289eb1bd","nodes":[{"object":"text","text":"Capital Structure in Perfect Capital Markets","marks":[]}],"data":{}}]}},"config":{"cssClass":""},"ref":"42d95d0e-3a1e-42ce-b9f1-4f5dfdadd299"}]}]},{"columns":[{"stageElements":[{"type":"stage-element-text","value":{"object":"value","document":{"object":"document","data":{},"nodes":[{"object":"block","type":"paragraph","ref":"e5e65f70-592b-43ef-8e65-3ece264e0f7d","nodes":[{"object":"text","text":"For problems in this section assume no taxes or distress costs.","marks":[{"type":"italic"}]}],"data":{}}]}},"config":{"cssClass":""},"ref":"d12a0a03-2076-4589-ad94-3e300bd55178"}]}]},{"columns":[{"stageElements":[{"type":"stage-element-text","value":{"object":"value","document":{"object":"document","data":{},"nodes":[{"object":"block","type":"ordered-list","data":{"listOptionType":"1","startValue":1},"ref":"a0aa056f-b767-4002-9156-b0dfa7f48b26","nodes":[{"object":"block","type":"list-item","data":{"direction":"auto"},"ref":"355ce48d-9fab-4e8b-944a-198a27c26183","nodes":[{"object":"block","type":"paragraph","ref":"dcf75b67-2293-4938-81ff-af8ff435ca94","nodes":[{"object":"text","text":"Consider a project with free cash flows in one year of $130,000 or $180,000, with each outcome being equally likely. The initial investment required for the project is $100,000, and the project’s cost of capital is 20%. The risk-free interest rate is 10%.","marks":[]}],"data":{}},{"object":"block","type":"ordered-list","data":{"listOptionType":"a","startValue":1},"ref":"6c6ba142-17e9-4cda-a470-ef23908b7d5f","nodes":[{"object":"block","type":"list-item","data":{"direction":"auto"},"ref":"b606de24-a399-484f-b498-a4b7c19b947b","nodes":[{"object":"block","type":"paragraph","ref":"fce89fd4-8d9a-4635-a889-d30a148a4bec","nodes":[{"object":"text","text":"What is the NPV of this project?","marks":[]}],"data":{}}]},{"object":"block","type":"list-item","data":{"direction":"auto"},"ref":"1acff57b-c762-4c02-8899-38e1b5a473f8","nodes":[{"object":"block","type":"paragraph","ref":"628587bd-b7a7-4546-bbd3-39b13a1c0c00","nodes":[{"object":"text","text":"Suppose that to raise the funds for the initial investment, the project is sold to investors as an all-equity firm. The equity holders will receive the cash flows of the project in one year. How much money can be raised in this way—that is, what is the initial market value of the unlevered equity?","marks":[]}],"data":{}}]},{"object":"block","type":"list-item","data":{"direction":"auto"},"ref":"37eb71f9-ada6-4bdf-b399-12799e7ec29a","nodes":[{"object":"block","type":"paragraph","ref":"ba3f79aa-8ae9-4e5c-9111-f7517c39f336","nodes":[{"object":"text","text":"Suppose the initial $100,000 is instead raised by borrowing at the risk-free interest rate. What are the cash flows of the levered equity, and what is its initial value according to MM?","marks":[]}],"data":{}}]}]}]},{"object":"block","type":"list-item","data":{"direction":"auto"},"ref":"cf2a7a36-95f7-4196-ba6a-1193645637a5","nodes":[{"object":"block","type":"paragraph","ref":"39312c37-9765-4ab3-b83a-45d0e7f49230","nodes":[{"object":"text","text":"You are an entrepreneur starting a biotechnology firm. If your research is successful, the technology can be sold for $30 million. If your research is unsuccessful, it will be worth nothing. To fund your research, you need to raise $2 million. Investors are willing to provide you with $2 million in initial capital in exchange for 50% of the unlevered equity in the firm.","marks":[]}],"data":{}},{"object":"block","type":"ordered-list","data":{"listOptionType":"a","startValue":1},"ref":"8d2c5968-6f4a-46ac-82eb-9eff68b42eab","nodes":[{"object":"block","type":"list-item","data":{"direction":"auto"},"ref":"ef0051bb-643f-419d-9c1d-d0675719ee92","nodes":[{"object":"block","type":"paragraph","ref":"3979b39c-fa72-4e48-98b0-20f2401b7dfb","nodes":[{"object":"text","text":"What is the total market value of the firm without leverage?","marks":[]}],"data":{}}]},{"object":"block","type":"list-item","data":{"direction":"auto"},"ref":"97e20d4f-ebf7-46c5-8970-7d303e62eca0","nodes":[{"object":"block","type":"paragraph","ref":"483af6d4-0827-4009-af7f-f52546cd80f9","nodes":[{"object":"text","text":"Suppose you borrow $1 million. According to MM, what fraction of the firm’s equity must you sell to raise the additional $1 million you need?","marks":[]}],"data":{}}]},{"object":"block","type":"list-item","data":{"direction":"auto"},"ref":"4b1f31ae-0a97-40e6-a50c-2dae1bc37da8","nodes":[{"object":"block","type":"paragraph","ref":"d7f85a78-631c-4f6e-b5fb-6ce0fc4e5817","nodes":[{"object":"text","text":"What is the value of your share of the firm’s equity in cases (a) and (b)?","marks":[]}],"data":{}}]}]}]},{"object":"block","type":"list-item","data":{"direction":"auto"},"ref":"9f614e77-fe9e-427f-8f1f-41ebcd4b6d81","nodes":[{"object":"block","type":"paragraph","ref":"dbe0a2e4-e77f-412f-8b9f-a040c0503678","nodes":[{"object":"text","text":"Acort Industries owns assets that will have an 80% probability of having a market value of $50 million in one year. There is a 20% chance that the assets will be worth only $20 million. The current risk-free rate is 5%, and Acort’s assets have a cost of capital of 10%.","marks":[]}],"data":{}},{"object":"block","type":"ordered-list","data":{"listOptionType":"a","startValue":1},"ref":"4eb1e8ab-1a1b-4e49-b652-e6ab707f4c2b","nodes":[{"object":"block","type":"list-item","data":{"direction":"auto"},"ref":"fda05690-8d7e-4671-a358-ee38049ab678","nodes":[{"object":"block","type":"paragraph","ref":"3270eb8b-738e-420f-825e-7be0d70bc7c1","nodes":[{"object":"text","text":"If Acort is unlevered, what is the current market value of its equity?","marks":[]}],"data":{}}]},{"object":"block","type":"list-item","data":{"direction":"auto"},"ref":"5ce7dcde-1fa0-4729-a19c-a56661bd701c","nodes":[{"object":"block","type":"paragraph","ref":"bdfdacf4-abfd-4bd0-9d1b-bb5f174a0c89","nodes":[{"object":"text","text":"Suppose instead that Acort has debt with a face value of $20 million due in one year. According to MM, what is the value of Acort’s equity in this case?","marks":[]}],"data":{}}]},{"object":"block","type":"list-item","data":{"direction":"auto"},"ref":"5815918b-e632-4a07-a005-b04966def036","nodes":[{"object":"block","type":"paragraph","ref":"72352d70-581a-4bbe-b63c-31f975dfa858","nodes":[{"object":"text","text":"What is the expected return of Acort’s equity without leverage? What is the expected return of Acort’s equity with leverage?","marks":[]}],"data":{}}]},{"object":"block","type":"list-item","data":{"direction":"auto"},"ref":"d1d97382-a676-40db-b4c4-4cb8e7f98796","nodes":[{"object":"block","type":"paragraph","ref":"b58ead3c-2da0-4873-a9e9-c0526cb12434","nodes":[{"object":"text","text":"What is the lowest possible realized return of Acort’s equity with and without leverage?","marks":[]}],"data":{}}]}]}]},{"object":"block","type":"list-item","data":{"direction":"auto"},"ref":"08542367-66b4-4b34-a515-b928812fa3c2","nodes":[{"object":"block","type":"paragraph","ref":"c7b73ee8-0390-4c03-982e-f3aae93c6a64","nodes":[{"object":"text","text":"Suppose there are no taxes. Firm ABC has no debt, and firm XYZ has debt of $5000 on which it pays interest of 10% each year. Both companies have identical projects that generate free cash flows of $800 or $1000 each year. After paying any interest on debt, both companies use all remaining free cash flows to pay dividends each year.","marks":[]}],"data":{}}]}]}]}},"config":{"cssClass":""},"ref":"3658cbd1-425a-4178-8339-69075795e9df"}]}]},{"columns":[{"stageElements":[{"type":"stage-element-table","config":{"activityLabel":"","instructions":"","tableCaptionText":"","activityTitle":"","tableTitle":"","captions":"","credit":""},"value":{"object":"value","document":{"object":"document","data":{},"nodes":[{"data":{},"nodes":[{"data":{},"nodes":[{"data":{},"nodes":[{"data":{"colSpan":1,"rowSpan":1},"nodes":[],"object":"block","type":"table-header","ref":"8ee40a03-059f-4ed3-8e6b-7450654f86ea"},{"data":{"colSpan":2,"rowSpan":1},"nodes":[{"object":"block","type":"paragraph","nodes":[{"object":"text","text":"ABC","marks":[]}],"data":{}}],"object":"block","type":"table-header","ref":"8d8b37ad-a34e-41af-b1c4-76b4fadb9056"},{"data":{"colSpan":2,"rowSpan":1},"nodes":[{"object":"block","type":"paragraph","nodes":[{"object":"text","text":"XYZ","marks":[]}],"data":{}}],"object":"block","type":"table-header","ref":"66a330ae-1652-468f-92ee-82b4ad413c09"}],"object":"block","type":"table-row","ref":"f447f4bd-fbea-410f-af6f-ab55273a3696"},{"data":{},"nodes":[{"data":{"colSpan":1,"rowSpan":1},"nodes":[{"object":"block","type":"paragraph","nodes":[{"object":"text","text":"FCF","marks":[]}],"data":{}}],"object":"block","type":"table-header","ref":"b264d08d-91b1-4eeb-8c0d-69204c96d585"},{"data":{"colSpan":1,"rowSpan":1},"nodes":[{"object":"block","type":"paragraph","nodes":[{"object":"text","text":"Debt Payments","marks":[]}],"data":{}}],"object":"block","type":"table-header","ref":"c379a954-0d55-43cb-a578-eaf057edf6bc"},{"data":{"colSpan":1,"rowSpan":1},"nodes":[{"object":"block","type":"paragraph","nodes":[{"object":"text","text":"Equity Dividends","marks":[]}],"data":{}}],"object":"block","type":"table-header","ref":"abd2a706-e1ca-4e78-8048-44c7f0ae1745"},{"data":{"colSpan":1,"rowSpan":1},"nodes":[{"object":"block","type":"paragraph","nodes":[{"object":"text","text":"Debt Payments","marks":[]}],"data":{}}],"object":"block","type":"table-header","ref":"7cd34128-41ba-4bf1-ab58-76a459752a9e"},{"data":{"colSpan":1,"rowSpan":1},"nodes":[{"object":"block","type":"paragraph","nodes":[{"object":"text","text":"Equity Dividends","marks":[]}],"data":{}}],"object":"block","type":"table-header","ref":"0d51e4ad-8c41-462e-b5fe-947c04c8ca7f"}],"object":"block","type":"table-row","ref":"97b64411-cc2f-4abc-92cf-732c0d82ecb6"}],"object":"block","type":"table-head","ref":"65a12e29-f996-4bbd-ae9f-bdf68f9f538e"},{"data":{},"nodes":[{"data":{},"nodes":[{"data":{"colSpan":1,"rowSpan":1},"nodes":[{"object":"block","type":"paragraph","nodes":[{"object":"text","text":"$ 800","marks":[]}],"data":{}}],"object":"block","type":"table-data","ref":"6970b2d0-4db8-438c-aa41-51504879edb0"},{"data":{"colSpan":1,"rowSpan":1},"nodes":[],"object":"block","type":"table-data","ref":"3816bed5-5f29-4ed8-82f1-ab2ae3172d00"},{"data":{"colSpan":1,"rowSpan":1},"nodes":[],"object":"block","type":"table-data","ref":"6aa9f178-1aa8-493f-944d-503a9162aa23"},{"data":{"colSpan":1,"rowSpan":1},"nodes":[],"object":"block","type":"table-data","ref":"f44b1b66-5d91-439a-9872-24651b48f51a"},{"data":{"colSpan":1,"rowSpan":1},"nodes":[],"object":"block","type":"table-data","ref":"8aa0d88e-7d1d-4e1d-a1de-677af749bb45"}],"object":"block","type":"table-row","ref":"4c002fdb-ceb1-48b3-986e-fc38fe2735a9"},{"data":{},"nodes":[{"data":{"colSpan":1,"rowSpan":1},"nodes":[{"object":"block","type":"paragraph","nodes":[{"object":"text","text":"$1000","marks":[]}],"data":{}}],"object":"block","type":"table-data","ref":"051f47c9-c52a-4cfd-8a6f-e5c5d0fa29da"},{"data":{"colSpan":1,"rowSpan":1},"nodes":[],"object":"block","type":"table-data","ref":"20a80091-6a87-4015-b75c-63a67628ed1e"},{"data":{"colSpan":1,"rowSpan":1},"nodes":[],"object":"block","type":"table-data","ref":"64653769-6c94-4195-902c-df5fa60eb8f4"},{"data":{"colSpan":1,"rowSpan":1},"nodes":[],"object":"block","type":"table-data","ref":"04cceae3-574b-4063-a70e-dc2bfb1fe5a5"},{"data":{"colSpan":1,"rowSpan":1},"nodes":[],"object":"block","type":"table-data","ref":"aefe5249-9155-43da-adf8-352325fa7180"}],"object":"block","type":"table-row","ref":"a1d2468f-9374-408f-b616-91f28d10a624"}],"object":"block","type":"table-body","ref":"cfd677fb-34b6-40f9-80ab-6a1d4f72bd6b"}],"object":"block","type":"table","ref":"a1eff15b-dfa2-4e08-b16f-b0b6bd0c1ce0"}]}},"ref":"3c5f4bca-b57e-4854-90e2-3f920f246b82"}]}]},{"columns":[{"stageElements":[{"type":"stage-element-text","value":{"object":"value","document":{"object":"document","data":{},"nodes":[{"object":"block","type":"ordered-list","data":{"listOptionType":"a","startValue":1},"ref":"a583e2e0-9eac-456f-8a61-742c36ef7592","nodes":[{"object":"block","type":"list-item","data":{"direction":"auto"},"ref":"c1a6c192-270f-4f9d-a583-94290726c51f","nodes":[{"object":"block","type":"paragraph","ref":"fa1e20f7-a6d6-49c8-b843-8f9d75ef8011","nodes":[{"object":"text","text":"Fill in the table above showing the debt payments and equity dividends each firm will receive given each of the two possible levels of free cash flows.","marks":[]}],"data":{}}]},{"object":"block","type":"list-item","data":{"direction":"auto"},"ref":"1922ff89-219b-48ff-b032-19b97e956ae7","nodes":[{"object":"block","type":"paragraph","ref":"aa005ce5-02d6-452c-a0a3-2523dc8f3fa2","nodes":[{"object":"text","text":"Suppose you hold 10% of the equity of ABC. What is another portfolio you could hold that would provide the same cash flows?","marks":[]}],"data":{}}]},{"object":"block","type":"list-item","data":{"direction":"auto"},"ref":"e2dc6142-0376-40c5-8e3c-1c0a3bdd8ff7","nodes":[{"object":"block","type":"paragraph","ref":"ffb8b89c-ecc0-42ae-a12b-382c154d4619","nodes":[{"object":"text","text":"Suppose you hold 10% of the equity of XYZ. If you can borrow at 10%, what is an alternative strategy that would provide the same cash flows?","marks":[]}],"data":{}}]}]}]}},"config":{"cssClass":""},"ref":"918c7699-0783-4fc1-93ee-8ae8587c60b7"}]}]},{"columns":[{"stageElements":[{"type":"stage-element-text","value":{"object":"value","document":{"object":"document","data":{},"nodes":[{"object":"block","type":"ordered-list","data":{"listOptionType":"1","startValue":5},"ref":"b7c912e8-e0db-407d-95d3-a215864b96ee","nodes":[{"object":"block","type":"list-item","data":{"direction":"auto"},"ref":"e9454b55-4564-437a-85be-7e65e74e3d57","nodes":[{"object":"block","type":"paragraph","ref":"ed986b3b-64ba-45f5-a945-381a51273b21","nodes":[{"object":"text","text":"Hardmon Enterprises is currently an all-equity firm with an expected return of 12%. It is considering borrowing money to buy back some of its existing shares, thus increasing its leverage.","marks":[]}],"data":{}},{"object":"block","type":"ordered-list","data":{"listOptionType":"a","startValue":1},"ref":"b2fc4146-3591-49bd-b00e-69bf943d7303","nodes":[{"object":"block","type":"list-item","data":{"direction":"auto"},"ref":"3e37cabe-491d-455b-b68e-5e100ca80578","nodes":[{"object":"block","type":"paragraph","ref":"8366809f-c40b-4688-9c72-c18b161a2074","nodes":[{"object":"text","text":"Suppose Hardmon borrows to the point that its debt-equity ratio is 0.50. With this amount of debt, the debt cost of capital is 6%. What will be the expected return of equity after this transaction?","marks":[]}],"data":{}}]},{"object":"block","type":"list-item","data":{"direction":"auto"},"ref":"56dead03-f61e-4f59-b1ce-fe19b63e4207","nodes":[{"object":"block","type":"paragraph","ref":"2177ac0b-3e73-42bd-a37b-9a4eb3c838ee","nodes":[{"object":"text","text":"Suppose instead Hardmon borrows to the point that its debt-equity ratio is 1.50. With this amount of debt, Hardmon’s debt will be much riskier. As a result, the debt cost of capital will be 8%. What will be the expected return of equity in this case?","marks":[]}],"data":{}}]},{"object":"block","type":"list-item","data":{"direction":"auto"},"ref":"621ed5af-fbe7-485a-b9c0-f5dd716684ba","nodes":[{"object":"block","type":"paragraph","ref":"57a3a954-1c14-455e-9814-03c8ef69e8a4","nodes":[{"object":"text","text":"A senior manager argues that it is in the best interest of the shareholders to choose the capital structure that leads to the highest expected return for the stock. How would you respond to this argument?","marks":[]}],"data":{}}]}]}]},{"object":"block","type":"list-item","data":{"direction":"auto"},"ref":"b43fef4e-a895-458f-bcb9-e47442704875","nodes":[{"object":"block","type":"paragraph","ref":"e7dc9d94-a9a0-4d55-9e98-c682fba2cec7","nodes":[{"object":"text","text":"Suppose Microsoft has no debt and a WACC of 9.2%. The average debt-to-value ratio for the software industry is 5%. What would be its cost of equity if it took on the average amount of debt for its industry at a cost of debt of 6%?","marks":[]}],"data":{}}]},{"object":"block","type":"list-item","data":{"direction":"auto"},"ref":"4166facb-b6d6-4f0f-b3be-b54ec279e5bd","nodes":[{"object":"block","type":"paragraph","ref":"23c2d4bf-39d7-46c0-b57b-221683bd830e","nodes":[{"object":"text","text":"Your firm is financed 100% with equity and has a cost of equity capital of 12%. You are considering your first debt issue, which would change your capital structure to 30% debt and 70% equity. If your cost of debt is 7%, what will be your new cost of equity?","marks":[]}],"data":{}}]},{"object":"block","type":"list-item","data":{"direction":"auto"},"ref":"b61fbe2f-6cdc-4b35-916f-b7188b1b9d88","nodes":[{"object":"block","type":"paragraph","ref":"41e7a890-3d14-449e-a9cb-8724df7107a1","nodes":[{"object":"text","text":"One of your new employees notes that your debt has a lower cost of capital (5%) than your equity (15%). So, he suggests that the firm swap its capital structure from 30% debt and 70% equity to 70% debt and 30% equity instead. He estimates that after the swap, your cost of equity would be 20%.","marks":[]}],"data":{}},{"object":"block","type":"ordered-list","data":{"listOptionType":"a","startValue":1},"ref":"fa299016-aedc-417c-aabe-fe295059dbe5","nodes":[{"object":"block","type":"list-item","data":{"direction":"auto"},"ref":"efe8e2bc-b8b5-4a60-9551-1f974d3ef178","nodes":[{"object":"block","type":"paragraph","ref":"13602909-59c5-4441-bb28-31f5abae88d2","nodes":[{"object":"text","text":"What would be your new cost of debt?","marks":[]}],"data":{}}]},{"object":"block","type":"list-item","data":{"direction":"auto"},"ref":"7d7c1fc2-edb4-45fc-8998-957a68d5a5e0","nodes":[{"object":"block","type":"paragraph","ref":"9a5bef74-e16b-4b67-add3-ff7f01e8a12b","nodes":[{"object":"text","text":"Have you lowered your overall cost of capital?","marks":[]}],"data":{}}]}]}]}]}]}},"config":{"cssClass":""},"ref":"3ee76837-4050-426f-ab57-6cf2bff139ff"}]}]}]}]},"screenType":"","transitions":{"enter":{"animation":"","duration":0,"easing":"","customKeyframes":""},"exit":{"animation":"","duration":0,"easing":"","customKeyframes":""}},"lockElements":false,"learnerCurrentAttempt":1,"footer":{"buttonText":"Next","buttonIcon":"Arrow","showFooter":false,"showHistoryNavButtons":false,"previewFooter":false,"position":"Fixed to screen bottom","footerComponent":{"showFooterDropArea":"hide","width":100,"footerComponentsAlignment":"right"}},"styles":{"background":{},"stage":{"maxWidth":940,"background":"rgba(255, 255, 255, 1)","responsive":true,"padding":{"vertical":60,"horizontal":60},"border":{"color":"rgba(224, 224, 224, 1)","radius":0,"width":0}},"elements":{"padding":{"vertical":10,"horizontal":10}},"footer":{"buttonColor":"rgba(0, 115, 202, 1)","textColor":"rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.7)","backgroundColor":"rgba(255, 255, 255, 1)","padding":10,"corners":4,"border":"none","shadow":"0 -1px 4px 0 rgba(0,0,0,0.06), 0 0 12px 2px rgba(0,0,0,0.1)"},"feedback":{"width":320,"textColor":"rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.7)","backgroundColor":"rgba(255, 255, 255, 1)","corners":4,"border":"none","shadow":"0 5px 47px 10px rgba(0,0,0,0.15), 0 10px 20px 2px rgba(0,0,0,0.1), 0 7px 8px 0 rgba(0,0,0,0.1)"}},"title":"Capital Structure in Perfect Capital Markets"},"assets":[],"scenarios":[],"pluginPayload":{"pluginRepositoryPath":"https://plugin-repository-bronte-qaint.pearson.com/9417ac60-5f60-11ea-8e69-affb2224d7e8/0.15.209/ac43ee4c0eda05e9718fa83a5aed4cff.zip","summary":{"pluginId":"9417ac60-5f60-11ea-8e69-affb2224d7e8","name":"Screen","description":"A screen of a lesson","type":"screen","latestVersion":"0.15.209","subscriptionId":"f0afd4d0-d2ff-11ea-9998-d57e1e28aca1","createdAt":"Fri, 6 Mar 2020 04:11:39 GMT","updatedAt":"Tue, 13 Dec 2022 22:07:46 GMT","tags":[],"publishMode":"DEFAULT"}},"activityThemeIconLibraries":[]}